K-means Clustering in R

R Code

# Load required package
set.seed(123)
data <- iris[, 1:4]  # Use only numeric features

# Apply k-means clustering
kmeans_result <- kmeans(data, centers = 3, nstart = 20)

# View results
print(kmeans_result$cluster)

# Compute first two principal components for visualization
pc <- prcomp(data)$x[, 1:2]

# Plot
plot(pc,
    col = kmeans_result$cluster, pch = 19,
    xlab = "PC1", ylab = "PC2", main = "K-means Clustering (k=3)"
)
points(kmeans_result$centers %*% prcomp(data)$rotation[, 1:2],
    col = 1:3, pch = 4, cex = 2, lwd = 2
)

Formula

\[ \underset{C}{\arg\min} \sum_{i=1}^{k} \sum_{x \in C_i} \| x - \mu_i \|^2 \]
